value.title: Kamala Harris Brings Hollywood Cash to Biden Campaign
value.excerpt: The California senator has close relationships with Democratic women and people of color in the entertainment industry, a dozen donors and fundraisers said.

value.title: Ben Shapiro: 2020 now a referendum on vengeful Democrats, not controversial Trump
value.excerpt: Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg's death last week immediately initiated a political firestorm in Washington, D.C.

value.title: Bernie Sanders plans news conference on Trump's 'threats' to democracy
value.excerpt: Sen. Bernie Sanders, I-Vt., announced Wednesday he plans to hold a news conference Thursday regarding what he described as President Trump's “threats” to democracy in the presidential election.

value.title: Trump blasts ballots when asked about election aftermath: 'The ballots are a disaster'
value.excerpt: President Trump Wednesday told reporters he would have to “see what happens” with election results before committing to a peaceful transfer of power.

value.title: Donald Trump Jr. condemns 'anarchy' in Louisville after officers shot amid Breonna Taylor protests
value.excerpt: Louisville, Ky., is the latest American city to see peaceful protests transform into violent riots and "anarchy," Donald Trump Jr. said Wednesday during an appearance on “Hannity”

value.title: Trump praises Kentucky governor's request for National Guard
value.excerpt: President Trump on Wednesday praised Kentucky’s Democratic Gov. Andy Beshear for calling in the National Guard just hours before a police officer was shot during protests following the grand jury decision in the Breonna Taylor case.

value.title: WSJ Opinion: Bork's Warning Over Judicial Activism Still Haunts Joe Biden
value.excerpt: Today we call Supreme Court nominee Robert Bork back from 1987 as witness to what has happened to American politics, and why we’re going to war ove

value.title: Coronavirus testing czar claims he's 'never been pressured' by Trump to 'change the guidance'
value.excerpt: Assistant Secretary for Health Adm. Brett Giroir told "The Story" Wednesday that he has never felt pressured by the Trump administration to alter public guidance about coronavirus.

value.title: Debate coach Brett O'Donnell reviews what could trip Trump up during debate with Biden
value.excerpt: Brett O'Donnell, a top GOP political debate coach said Wednesday that President Trump should be vigilant in his upcoming debate with Joe Biden, by steering clear of certain issues which might tank his White House reelection chances.

value.title: Trump exits news briefing for 'emergency phone call' after being pressed on Breonna Taylor case
value.excerpt: President Trump exited his news conference Wednesday, telling reporters he had an “emergency” phone call as they continued to heckle him with questions, particularly on the Breonna Taylor case.

value.title: Eric Trump must testify in New York AG probe before election, judge rules
value.excerpt: A judge ruled Wednesday that Eric Trump must testify before the election in response to a subpoena from the New York attorney general’s office as part of an investigation into whether the Trump organization improperly valued real estate assets in statements.

value.title: Joe Biden’s Proposed Spending Comes With a High Cost
value.excerpt: Until Congress gets spending under control, any proposals for vast new government programs should be dismissed as dangerous and immoral seductions.

value.title: Kamala Harris criticized for lack of press availability: ‘What are they afraid of?’
value.excerpt: It’s been well over a month since 2020 Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden selected Sen. Kamala Harris as his running mate and critics on both sides of the aisle are starting to wonder why she hasn’t been more accessible to the media.

value.title: Trump planning executive orders on health care to protect preexisting conditions
value.excerpt: President Trump is preparing to issue a series of executive actions on health care "in the weeks ahead" as his administration fights to repeal ObamaCare in the Supreme Court.

value.title: Milwaukee suburbs could be key for Trump re-election
value.excerpt: As more of American suburbia reportedly tilts toward Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden ahead of the November election, the suburbs on the outskirts of Milwaukee remain a bulwark of support for President Trump.

value.title: Trump implements new travel restrictions to Cuba, bans purchase of rum and tobacco
value.excerpt: President Trump announced new restrictions for American travelers going to Cuba, barring them from purchasing rum and tobacco or staying in Cuban government-funded hotels.

value.title: Trey Gowdy rips Biden: ‘If you want to pick Supreme Court justices, win elections’
value.excerpt: Trey Gowdy told "Fox & Friends" President Trump is right to nominate a Supreme Court justice before the election.

value.title: "Lincoln Project" Ad Blasts "Draft Dodger" Donald Trump In Ad Targeting Military Members
value.excerpt: Trump GOP group "The Lincoln Project" will be running this ad in military magaxine "Stars & Stripes" and on the Military Times Network through mid-October.

value.title: Biden says he'll begin prepping for debate ‘really heavily’ on Thursday
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden said on Wednesday that he’s begun to prepare for next week’s presidential debate, but that more intense preparation begins on Thursday.

value.title: MSNBC’s Donny Deutsch compares Trump to Hitler, blasts Jewish Americans who support him
value.excerpt: MSNBC mainstay Donny Deutsch compared President Trump to Adolf Hitler on Wednesday morning and blasted Jewish Americans who plan to vote for him in November.

value.title: Judd Apatow, Rob Reiner accuse Donald Trump of 'mass murder' in separate tweets
value.excerpt: Filmmakers Judd Apatow and Rob Reiner took to Twitter on Tuesday to accuse Donald Trump of dishonesty and murder.

value.title: Gorsuch, Kavanaugh 'didn't really tip' Supreme Court balance, Trump advisers say in new book
value.excerpt: Because both Gorsuch and Kavanaugh replaced Republican-appointed justices, David Bossie and Cory Lewandowski say, a second Trump term in which he may have the chance to replace Democrat-appointed justices could be more impactful.

value.title: GOP-led committees release interim report on Hunter Biden, Burisma probe
value.excerpt: The Senate Homeland Security and Finance Committees on Wednesday released an interim report on their monthslong joint investigation into Hunter Biden’s role on the board of Ukrainian natural gas firm Burisma Holdings.

value.title: Ilhan Omar fires back after Trump's rally attack: 'This is my country'
value.excerpt: Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., fired back at President Trump on Tuesday night after he told a rally crowd she was lecturing Republicans on how to run the country and referenced her native Somalia.

value.title: Why Biden is sidestepping SCOTUS fight, won’t embrace court-packing
value.excerpt: Joe Biden’s lead in the presidential race hasn’t changed all that much since he surged to the nomination, and the last few days help explain why.

value.title: McMaster warns Trump plays 'into Putin's hands' with warm remarks about Russian president
value.excerpt: President Trump should be harder on Russian President Vladimir Putin in his public statements, former National Security Adviser H.R. McMaster argued on "The Story" Tuesday.

value.title: Trump on SCOTUS nominee: 'Watch the abuse she will take'
value.excerpt: President Trump told supporters in Pennsylvania to “watch the abuse” his nominee for the Supreme Court would take after he released her name on Saturday.

value.title: Cindy McCain, wife of late GOP senator, is endorsing Joe Biden
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden announced Tuesday that Cindy McCain, the wife of late Republican Sen. John McCain, is endorsing his presidential bid following President Trump’s alleged remarks about U.S. services members as reported by The Atlantic.

value.title: China fumes at Trump’s UN speech, accuses US of spreading 'political virus'
value.excerpt: China on Tuesday responded angrily to President Trump’s speech at the U.N. General Assembly, in which he blamed the communist country for the coronavirus pandemic -- with Beijing accusing Trump of spreading a “political virus.”

value.title: Karl Rove breaks down Trump, Biden's pursuit of Midwest working-class voters
value.excerpt: President Trump and Joe Biden spent Monday making campaign appearances in different Midwestern states to court the working-class vote, former George W. Bush adviser Karl Rove explained on "Bill Hemmer Reports" Tuesday.
